cs.SY, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CE 

The paper deals with data-driven models for power grid analysis, which involves the use of machine learning and optimization techniques. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.SY (Systems and Control), which deals with the modeling, analysis, and control of complex systems. The paper also proposes an evaluation implementation based on Rademacher complexity theory, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of partial physical knowledge to reduce the required amount of data, which involves the use of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and network engineering (cs.NE) techniques. Finally, the paper deals with power grid analysis, which falls under the category of computer engineering (cs.CE).
